        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 5:28AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 528 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Emerson, or near
Cartersville, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to exposed surfaces is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cartersville, Kennesaw, Acworth, Emerson, George Washington Carver St
Pk, Kellogg Creek, Red Top Mountain State Park, and Oak Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
